President Obama called King Abdullah bin Abdulaziz Al-Saud of Saudi Arabia to convey his best wishes as Ramadan begins. They discussed the current situation in Iraq and the threat that ISIL poses to the stability of Iraq and the region. They emphasized the need for Iraq's leaders to form a new government that can unite all communities. The President thanked the King for Saudi Arabia's pledge of $500 million to help displaced Iraqis. They agreed to continue consulting on regional developments.